    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty blunt take lol. so when historians talk about it being a failure, do they mostly just blame the veto power and structural stuff, or are there people who actually argue that international organizations are just fundamentally flawed and shouldn't have that much influence on sovereign nations?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
